JOHANNESBURG – Police arrested three people on Thursday in a crime prevention operation on hijacked buildings in Jeppestown, East of Johannesburg. Several buildings were targeted, including Maria Park on Janie Street, and Casino Hotel. One suspect was arrested for being in possession two rounds of ammunition while two suspects were arrested for possession of drugs.  Three vehicles were also impounded during the operation. READ: More than 100 people arrested in raids on Joburg hijacked buildings Several shops in the area were also raided resulting in five compliance notices issued to shop owners, a fine was issued to a shop owner by EMS, and one-second hand goods shop was issued with a notice to close down.  The city said that no undocumented foreign nationals were arrested during the operation because the Department of Home Affairs did not participate in the operation. eNCA